 objection in providing medical services. The volume approaches this problem from an interdisciplinary perspective and elucidates the diverse dimensions of decisions of conscience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aHealthxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMedical ethics. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh  aEthics.  aclinical equipoise.  aconscience.  ahealth care.1 aBaumann, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Gerhild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBentele, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergdolt, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBormann, Franz-Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBormann, Franz-Josef, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBuch, Alois Joh., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuttge, Gunnar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEibach, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErnst, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFonk, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForschner, Maximilian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrick, Eckhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGertrud, Nunner-Winkler, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiese, Constanze, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHack, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenn, Wolfram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerzberg, Stephan, econtr